<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-09-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-09-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="1196" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1196">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.93/45.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Chinese Chargé
                                    d’Affaires</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of China</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-09-23">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 23, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I beg to acknowledge
                            the receipt of your note of September 19th informing me [etc.] the
                            substance of which I telegraphed to my Government for its information,
                            and in reply thereto I have been directed to ask the Department to
                            instruct the <pb facs="1025" n="921" xml:id="pg_921"/> American Consul
                            at Durango to render such assistance as may be necessary to those
                            Chinese who are destitute and needing help, and that the Legation will
                            be glad to reimburse the Department for such expense as may be
                            incurred.</p>
                        <p>I beg [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Chang Kang-jen</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Note</hi>.—The Consul was instructed as above
                                requested, on September 26.</p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>